Title: Tasmanian Gravity Data (P199552), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Tasmanian Gravity Data (P199552) contains a total of 415 point data values acquired at a spacing between 3000 and 5000 metres. The data is located in TAS and were acquired in 1995, under project No. 199552 for Geological Survey of Tasmania (Mineral Resources Tasmania).

Lineage: This Tasmanian Gravity Data (P199552), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Tasmanian Gravity Data (P199552) survey acquired for Geological Survey of Tasmania (Mineral Resources Tasmania). This dataset contains a total of 415 point data values. The data is located in TAS and were acquired in 1995. The point located data were collected in traverse layout at a station spacing between 3000 and 5000 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.
SourceDescription: This Tasmanian Gravity Data (P199552), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Tasmanian Gravity Data (P199552) survey acquired for Geological Survey of Tasmania (Mineral Resources Tasmania).

Lineage: This EL2741 Roopena, SA, Detailed Gravity Survey 1995,1992A10 (P199556), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the EL2741 Roopena, SA, Detailed Gravity Survey 1995,1992A10 (P199556) survey acquired for Western Mining Corporation Ltd. This dataset contains a total of 1379 point data values. The data is located in SA and were acquired in 1995. The point located data were collected in grids layout at a station spacing between 100 and 400 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.

Title: SA Detailed Gravity Survey 95A2 (P199572), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This SA Detailed Gravity Survey 95A2 (P199572) contains a total of 2830 point data values acquired at a spacing between 500 and 1000 metres. The data is located in SA and were acquired in 1995, under project No. 199572 for None.
